ions to the semiclassical setting and give a\ndescription of the kernel of the free resolvent as such a distribution. We also\nconstruct a semiclassical version of the Melrose--Taylor parametrix for complex\nenergies. We use these constructions to give a complete microlocal description\nof boundary layer operators and to prove sharp high energy estimates on the\nboundary layer operators in the case that $\\partial\\Omega$ is smooth and\nstrictly convex.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 14 Apr 2014 19:33:13 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 7 May 2014 00:37:53 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 14 Jul 2014 03:11:44 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Wed, 15 Oct 2014 00:49:05 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Mon, 14 Sep 2015 01:28:50 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-09-15"}
